4) that the grant in any one year amount to no more than $1000;=20

5) that the grant in any one year amount to no more than half the cost of t=
he equipment being purchased by the club in that year;=20

6) that the membership be informed of the existence of the program by appro=
priate announcements, and that the parameters of the program be clearly spe=
cified in a permanent location accessible through the internet;=20

7) that applicants be requested to provide specific information about their=
 programs to the CC Membership Committee when applying, and that the Member=
ship Committee review the applications and make recommendations to the Boar=
d for final disposition, in a timely fashion;=20

8) that the funds disbursed by Croquet Canada be paid directly by Croquet C=
anada to the supplier(s) of the equipment as partial payment for the order(=
s) made;=20

9) that the equipment be purchased from suppliers located in Canada;=20

10) that no restrictions be made as to whether the supplier(s) are commerci=
al providers, private individuals, or other clubs selling equipment surplus=
 to their needs; and=20

11) that Croquet Canada approves of the suppliers as providing reasonable v=
alue for the funds Croquet Canada provides.=20

