de information. Here are the questions we would like the Abbotsford club to=
 answer. While you are gathering this information, I=E2=80=99ll check with =
the board and see how our financial situation looks in terms of providing s=
upport. I should have a reasonable answer to that in a few days.=20

The questions:=20


1) To your knowledge, how many croquet clubs with lawns of reasonable quali=
ty already exist in your city?=20

2) How many lawns will be available at your club for croquet play, and how =
often?=20

3) How many members do you hope to have playing croquet on a fairly regular=
 basis during the next year?=20

4) What sports are currently played regularly at your club?=20

5) Will your club be willing to accept members who want to join only to pla=
y croquet?=20

6) How much are you willing to spend over the next year to get your croquet=
 program up and running?=20

7) Are you interested in exchanging information with other clubs, hosting v=
isiting experts who can help your players improve, and sending your members=
 to other clubs for tournaments, friendly play, or training?=20
There are probably other questions that would be germane, but I think these=
